Package org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.api

Enum ConnectionType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ConnectionType>
      • org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.api.ConnectionType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ConnectionType>
    public enum ConnectionType
extends Enum<ConnectionType>
    Defines the types of connections factories that should be used to provide connections to callers.

    When adding a new ConnectionType, you will need to add a new default configuration class, and both the ConnectionCount and TimeoutConfig logic for deducing how many connections to allocate and with what timeout will also need to be updated.

    When customising the data layer for a particular type (i.e. to use a non-LDAP backend), you will need to implement a separate implementation of the configuration class and all the different types it configures, as well as setting a system property of org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.[ConnectionType.name()].
